### JavaScript Canvas:
1. <canvas> allows developers to chive 2D graphics.
2. A closing </closing> tag is important because any content between the opening and closing tag is fallback content that will display only if the browser doesn't support the <canvas> element.
3. The getContext() method takes one argument, which is the type of content, and it returns a render context object.

### Charts.js Documentation:
1. Charts.js is an easy way of creating HTML-based charts. This can be brought to my project when attempting to create data visualization.
2. Three different Chart types you can create using Chart.js. are scatter charts, bubble charts, and area charts.

### Easily Create Stunning Animated Charts With Charts.js:
1. One advantage to displaying data via chart over a table is that it is easier to look at and convey data quickly.
2. It will help data more easier to read and understand.

